Description: Corroded iron tanged arrow-head of triangular section with a cylindro-conical part between the head and the tang, most of which is probably missing.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 78 § 77, p. 110, pl. xxxvii, 12)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.69, p.70, p.183, pl.25)
